A trainee pilot and an instructor had a dramatic escape when their plane crash-landed at an air base.

The two-person Tucano trainer crashed on its approach to the runway when its undercarriage failed to come down.

Amazingly both men walked away unhurt but the turbo-prop Tucano, which is driven by a propellor powered by a jet engine, suffered serious damage and came to rest on grass after travelling down the runway.

